President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Alabama due to the emergency conditions caused by Hurricane Sally. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts in order to alleviate hardship and suffering. Public Assistance Category B emergency protective measures, including direct Federal assistance, will be provided for multiple counties in Alabama, as well as the Poarch Band of Creek Indians. Additionally, limited direct Federal assistance will be provided for several other counties. Allan Jarvis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.